			mSpellDescriptions.add(new SpellDescriptionRecord("Summon Demon I", "Using this spell (plus opening a demonic portal), the mage may summon a lesser demon from the realm of Sylkree. The mage must know the name of the demon and call it out when casting the spell. The mage has a Success Rate of 15% +5% x level. Add +5% for an animal sacrifice. Add +10% for a human(oid) sacrifice. Add +5% more if female (and the demon is male) or male (and the demon is female). Add +10% more if virgin (either sex). The demon will have 3 to 4 levels and an approximate Armor Rating of 80%. The specifics on this demon should be worked out by your referee as no two demons are exactly alike. The demon appears through the \"Demonic Portal\". The mage must successfully roll a \"control check\" (same chance as he had to summon it) in order to command the demon (hell, just to keep it from killing the first 20 things it sees!). 10% is deducted from the mage's success with control each DAY the demon is maintained on this plane (so a mage with a 105% chance for control could almost guarantee control for 1 day (don't forget a \"00\" always fails)). The same demon may be summoned more than once.")); //$NON-NLS-1$ //$NON-NLS-2$
